narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, this course was a good foundation for mathematics at Yale and I enjoyed the breadth of topics covered in it.
Yes, this class was at the perfect pace for a student who has not taken calculus yet.

I would definitely recommend it to other students. The MATH 110 and MATH 111 sequence is simply a well taught sequence with interesting content. You do have to put from your part to understand some of the materials but the Professors and undergraduate learning assistants are always there to help you!
